      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my nest thermostat is acting weird. i didnt set any schedules but it keeps dropping the temp way down like at 3am every night. any idea why it would just reset itself like that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a bit of a mystery, but I can try to help you troubleshoot. It's possible that your thermostat has a built-in \"night mode\" or a \"low power\" setting that's kicking in, even without a scheduled override. You know, like a sneaky little goblin that likes to mess with your settings while you're sleeping. It's a common issue with smart thermostats, and it might be worth checking the app to see if there are any hidden settings or features that could be causing the problem.\n\nOne thing you can try is checking the thermostat's settings for any unusual or default settings that might be causing it to drop the temperature at night. You can also try resetting the thermostat to its factory settings and then reconfiguring it to see if that resolves the issue. It's a bit like trying to outsmart a mischievous goblin who's been messing with your thermostat – you have to outsmart it and get to the bottom of the problem!",
